1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,051
It was Frege in the 19th century, who first realized

2
00:00:04,151 --> 00:00:08,658
that mathematics involved manipulations involving a specific set of symbols.

3
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:11,250
These included the logical symbols such as the

4
00:00:11,350 --> 00:00:15,346
boolean connectives: conjunction, disjunction, implication and negation:

5
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:18,095
The quantifiers forall and exists

6
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:18,999
The variables

7
00:00:19,066 --> 00:00:20,037
And finally brackets

8
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:22,593
The non-logical symbols include the constants,

9
00:00:22,693 --> 00:00:24,709
function symbols and relation symbols:

10
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:27,960
The reason for the distinction, is that the non-logical symbols are

11
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:30,637
specific to a given theory. So, if we just restrict our

12
00:00:30,737 --> 00:00:33,411
attention to the logical symbols, we are in the domain of

13
00:00:33,511 --> 00:00:36,428
logic, since whatever we prove holds in all possible theories.

14
00:00:36,466 --> 00:00:38,863
Now, if we restrict ourselves further, omitting the

15
00:00:38,963 --> 00:00:40,870
quantifiers, then we are in the domain of

16
00:00:40,970 --> 00:00:43,367
Propositional logic, also known as 0th order logic.

17
00:00:43,466 --> 00:00:45,565
In fact we can prove that if we only use

18
00:00:45,665 --> 00:00:48,643
implies and negation we don't lose any expressive power.

19
00:00:49,733 --> 00:00:52,081
Here we can write down a propositional sentence phi

20
00:00:52,181 --> 00:00:55,249
by combining propositional variables according to the connectives.

21
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:57,618
In classical logic, to check if phi is true, we can

22
00:00:57,718 --> 00:01:00,097
simply create the truth table and check if there is a

23
00:01:00,197 --> 00:01:03,043
satisfying assignment, that is, a row where our formulas are 1.

24
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:06,123
We can check if it is valid, by checking if all

25
00:01:06,223 --> 00:01:08,275
of the rows evaluate to 1. This truth table can be

26
00:01:08,375 --> 00:01:10,212
seen as a model in which this sentence holds.

27
00:01:11,266 --> 00:01:13,306
In classical logic, this truth assignment is black and white. Display the truth table

28
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:14,614
for phi implies psi, a 2 by 2 matrix with 1s and 0s.

29
00:01:14,666 --> 00:01:16,794
We can generalize to create a many-valued logic, where the

30
00:01:16,894 --> 00:01:19,061
concept of truth is stretched out over an arbitrary number.

31
00:01:19,161 --> 00:01:20,444
Extend the matrix one box at a time.

32
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:21,516
It can even be a real number between 0 and 1. Now make

33
00:01:21,616 --> 00:01:23,202
there be an open interval and display something resembling a color selection window.

